1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,119
Beautiful music, I appreciate it, it's sung well and appropriately done, very good.

2
00:00:10,119 --> 00:00:16,120
I was surprised this morning, I was not included, I'm not going to be here for the apple picking

3
00:00:16,120 --> 00:00:17,639
trip.

4
00:00:17,639 --> 00:00:23,600
I want you to know that I am an apple connoisseur and an apple snob.

5
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:32,439
I literally eat an apple every day of my life and if you get the opportunity when you go

6
00:00:32,439 --> 00:00:39,520
out to the orchard, if they have ambrosia, go pick some ambrosias.

7
00:00:39,520 --> 00:00:47,200
If you like crisp, sweet apples, look for Envy and go buy or get some Envy apples.

8
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:51,279
Now if you want to know more about apples, see me after the service, okay?

9
00:00:51,279 --> 00:00:58,240
I honestly, I just finished a book on Johnny Appleseed and there really was a Johnny Appleseed

10
00:00:58,240 --> 00:01:05,599
and he was a great man and his vision was that some of the settlers going over the mountains,

11
00:01:05,599 --> 00:01:11,400
the pioneers, were so poor, so impoverished just to get to where they were going that

12
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:15,800
they would have no good food supply or it would be difficult for them to do.

13
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:22,000
He literally planted orchards all through the Appalachians, the Alleghenies, the Blue Ridge,

14
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:28,879
so that as they went, they could take twigs and branches and then replant and his vision

15
00:01:28,879 --> 00:01:33,480
was if they did that everywhere this side of the Mississippi, at least people would

16
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:37,319
have some good fruit and some good food for their life.

17
00:01:37,319 --> 00:01:44,959
So there are and were some good people with a good vision to be kind and helpful to others.

18
00:01:45,120 --> 00:01:48,000
Alright, that's the nicest I'm going to be all morning, alright?

19
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,639
I'm going to preach now.

20
00:01:49,639 --> 00:01:52,839
It is an absolute privilege and honor to be here.

21
00:01:52,839 --> 00:01:56,540
Pastor, thank you for this opportunity and invitation.

22
00:01:56,540 --> 00:02:01,839
Thank you for being here and I'm looking forward to what God is going to do in our midst.

23
00:02:01,839 --> 00:02:07,519
I'm asking God to speak to me, help me as much as I'm asking for God to speak to you

24
00:02:07,519 --> 00:02:09,039
and help you.

25
00:02:09,039 --> 00:02:15,119
Having said all that, Psalm 31 this morning, Psalm 31.

26
00:02:15,119 --> 00:02:19,559
And for our text, though we'll look at other verses, we're going to begin reading in verse

27
00:02:19,559 --> 00:02:27,759
14, Psalm 31 and verse 14.

28
00:02:27,759 --> 00:02:35,000
And there the Bible says this, David speaking under the inspiration of the Spirit of God,

29
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:44,600
But I trusted in Thee, O Lord, I said, Thou art my God.

30
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:50,320
My times are in Thy hand.

31
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:56,500
Deliver me from the hand of mine enemies, and from them that persecute me.

32
00:02:56,500 --> 00:03:04,279
Make Thy face to shine upon Thy servant, and save me for Thy mercy's sake.

33
00:03:04,279 --> 00:03:05,279
Let's pray.

34
00:03:05,279 --> 00:03:10,679
Father, we're very grateful for the opportunity to be together this morning.

35
00:03:10,679 --> 00:03:15,000
We thank You for Your Holy Spirit.

36
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:22,639
I pray that He this morning would take Your Word and speak to our hearts through it.

37
00:03:22,639 --> 00:03:27,800
Lord, we're gathered here because we know we need to hear from You.

38
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:30,679
And I pray that You would accomplish that.

39
00:03:30,679 --> 00:03:33,660
I ask You to encourage people.

40
00:03:33,660 --> 00:03:37,000
I pray that You would instruct people.

41
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:41,100
But I also pray that You would convict and challenge us.

42
00:03:41,100 --> 00:03:48,940
And Lord, where You see something in our life that needs to be strengthened, changed, would

43
00:03:48,940 --> 00:03:54,320
You convict us about that and then help us to accomplish what You want.

44
00:03:54,320 --> 00:04:00,979
I pray especially for those that may be here this morning in our presence that have never

45
00:04:00,979 --> 00:04:03,539
trusted Christ as their Savior.

46
00:04:03,539 --> 00:04:07,740
God, would You expose to them their great need.

47
00:04:07,740 --> 00:04:13,100
Beyond their need, would You reveal to them how much You love them and how much You desire

48
00:04:13,100 --> 00:04:15,059
to save them.

49
00:04:15,059 --> 00:04:18,059
So Lord, work in all of our hearts.

50
00:04:18,059 --> 00:04:19,579
Help us, we pray.

51
00:04:19,579 --> 00:04:23,339
In Jesus' name, amen.

52
00:04:23,339 --> 00:04:25,220
Here's my question to begin the message.

53
00:04:25,220 --> 00:04:31,779
In verse 14, David says, but I trusted in Thee.

54
00:04:31,779 --> 00:04:37,820
Why is David saying he's in a place where he has to bring attention to the fact that

55
00:04:37,820 --> 00:04:40,059
he's trusting in the Lord?

56
00:04:40,059 --> 00:04:43,220
Well the answer is in verse 9.

57
00:04:43,220 --> 00:04:51,540
Have mercy upon me, O Lord, for I am in trouble.

58
00:04:51,540 --> 00:04:57,540
The trouble that David is in and the word that he uses is not indicative that it's a

59
00:04:57,540 --> 00:04:59,739
difficult moment but it'll pass.

60
00:04:59,739 --> 00:05:03,179
No, he is in real trouble.

61
00:05:03,179 --> 00:05:10,579
We're not sure if this is from the time of his life when Saul was chasing him.

62
00:05:10,579 --> 00:05:17,579
We suspect and I agree that it is probably written around the time where Absalom has

63
00:05:17,739 --> 00:05:24,579
rebelled and David is being cast out of his palace, cast out of his city.

64
00:05:24,579 --> 00:05:31,179
Deceitfully, Absalom has asked leave, to go to leave the city.

65
00:05:31,179 --> 00:05:37,200
He's gone to Hebron, taken Hebron, taken that fortified city, raised an army and is now

66
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:40,420
marching back towards Jerusalem.

67
00:05:40,420 --> 00:05:45,100
There are people that are making decisions that are certainly terrible decisions for

68
00:05:45,100 --> 00:05:45,700
David.

69
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:47,339
They're forsaking him.

70
00:05:47,339 --> 00:05:51,859
They fear that Absalom's army is stronger than anything David has.

71
00:05:51,859 --> 00:05:55,980
David is aging and David is feeling forsaken.

72
00:05:55,980 --> 00:05:58,899
Notice what he says in verse 10.

73
00:05:58,899 --> 00:06:05,579
For my life is spent with grief, my years with sighing, my strength faileth because

74
00:06:05,579 --> 00:06:08,859
of mine iniquity, all my bones are consumed.

75
00:06:08,859 --> 00:06:15,100
I was a reproach among all my enemies but especially among my neighbors.

76
00:06:15,579 --> 00:06:22,579
Now I read that just so that we understand this is a deep moment of trouble in David's

77
00:06:24,059 --> 00:06:31,059
life and he is really concerned about what is going to happen to him, happen to his family.

78
00:06:32,019 --> 00:06:39,019
It is a serious moment into which he interjects this, but I trusted God.

79
00:06:39,579 --> 00:06:42,179
Why did you trust God David?

80
00:06:42,179 --> 00:06:48,540
Because my times are in His hands.

81
00:06:48,540 --> 00:06:53,579
David realized what you and I realized, that one of the realities of our lives in this

82
00:06:53,579 --> 00:06:57,940
world is that we experience seasons of stress.

83
00:06:57,940 --> 00:07:01,660
We experience seasons of trouble.

84
00:07:01,660 --> 00:07:07,500
We're surrounded by difficult moments, difficult times, problems if you will.

85
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:14,500
In our nation today, who cannot realize the difficulty of the moment we're in, the social

86
00:07:15,260 --> 00:07:17,619
unrest.

87
00:07:17,619 --> 00:07:23,380
Not only is there social unrest, political unrest, there's economic uncertainty.

88
00:07:23,380 --> 00:07:25,779
Who knows what interest rates are going to do?

89
00:07:25,779 --> 00:07:30,179
Who knows what this is going to have, what this bubble is going to bust?

90
00:07:30,179 --> 00:07:34,100
It's always a question of what's going to happen.

91
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:40,540
We've lived through a pandemic, now we're back into seasons of war.

92
00:07:40,540 --> 00:07:42,179
What's going to break next?

93
00:07:42,179 --> 00:07:46,140
Where will there be strife and killing next?

94
00:07:46,140 --> 00:07:49,940
There's situations specific to our own lives.

95
00:07:49,940 --> 00:07:51,940
Jobs change.

96
00:07:51,940 --> 00:07:55,040
Things in our circumstances of health change.

97
00:07:55,040 --> 00:08:02,040
There's just always this possibility of a season of stress.

98
00:08:02,359 --> 00:08:05,160
Have I encouraged you yet?

99
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:06,959
We'll get to it.

100
00:08:06,959 --> 00:08:13,519
That's why David said, man, we live in this ever-changing sea.

101
00:08:13,519 --> 00:08:18,480
We live where we just don't know what tomorrow's going to bring.

102
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:24,679
I had someone say to me, they said, preacher, it just seems like everything is as hard as

103
00:08:24,679 --> 00:08:27,000
it can be.

104
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,640
Sometimes we feel like that.

105
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:34,840
I noticed in the last song that we sang, a guy said, man, I feel like I'm dead.

106
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:38,919
But then Jesus comes and rolls the clouds away.

107
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:43,919
We understand that Jesus always knew where we were and always knew what we needed.

108
00:08:43,919 --> 00:08:48,080
We're not the first generation to face stress and trouble.

109
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:52,679
I doubt that many have faced all that David faced in his life.

110
00:08:52,679 --> 00:08:59,080
As a young man, he had to face and kill a bear and a lion and a giant.

111
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:03,520
As a young king, Saul was determined to kill him.

112
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:05,320
He had a kingdom to manage.

113
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:10,679
He was surrounded all of his days as king with wars and fighting.

114
00:09:10,679 --> 00:09:14,520
He had a very difficult family situation, some of his own making.

115
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:22,960
But my point is this, that in life, if you and I think that it is always a fairy tale,

116
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:25,080
it is not so.

117
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:32,919
And how is it that we as believers today, how do we manage these seasons of stress,

118
00:09:32,919 --> 00:09:39,239
these seasons of difficulty, and it comes back to the statement that he trusted in the

119
00:09:39,239 --> 00:09:46,599
Lord because his times, David's, were in God's hands.

120
00:09:46,599 --> 00:09:50,760
And I want you to know that though we are not fighting giants and killing bears and

121
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:57,159
lions and we're not kings of kingdoms, we are people who live on God's earth and we

122
00:09:57,159 --> 00:10:00,039
do face the seasons of difficulty in our lives.

123
00:10:00,039 --> 00:10:06,359
lives and one of the great things that you and I must come to understand is that we can

124
00:10:06,359 --> 00:10:14,699
trust that God is our God and our seasons, our lives are lived in God's hands.

125
00:10:14,699 --> 00:10:16,839
Notice those two things with me today.

126
00:10:16,839 --> 00:10:20,359
Number one, my times.

127
00:10:20,359 --> 00:10:26,319
David's life and our lives are definitely marked by change and instability.

128
00:10:26,319 --> 00:10:33,559
That word that David used for times is a word that indicates seasons or changeableness.

129
00:10:33,559 --> 00:10:35,959
I'll speak more about that in a moment.

130
00:10:35,959 --> 00:10:42,919
But I just want you to recognize this morning that our lives are lived in seasons.

131
00:10:42,919 --> 00:10:47,399
Let me try to illustrate it.

132
00:10:47,399 --> 00:10:52,279
Several years ago, I was born an infant, more than several.

133
00:10:52,279 --> 00:10:57,079
And in infancy, I was completely helpless.

134
00:10:57,079 --> 00:11:02,519
If my mother and father had not provided for me, had there not been a gracious God, I couldn't

135
00:11:02,519 --> 00:11:03,839
have survived.

136
00:11:03,839 --> 00:11:04,839
But you know what?

137
00:11:04,839 --> 00:11:09,759
I grew out of that age of infancy and I became a toddler.

138
00:11:09,759 --> 00:11:13,179
And I was such a precious toddler.

139
00:11:13,179 --> 00:11:15,159
You know the season of being a toddler.

140
00:11:15,159 --> 00:11:17,039
It's a challenging season.

141
00:11:17,039 --> 00:11:18,039
But you know what?

142
00:11:18,039 --> 00:11:22,279
We grow out of being toddlers and we become juniors.

143
00:11:22,279 --> 00:11:27,639
And as juniors, the world is exciting and life is exciting and mom and dad are great

144
00:11:27,639 --> 00:11:30,279
and it's a wonderful season of life.

145
00:11:30,279 --> 00:11:34,519
But we grow out of being juniors and we become teenagers.

146
00:11:34,519 --> 00:11:39,159
And we then understand that it's our job to teach mother and dad how they're to live and

147
00:11:39,159 --> 00:11:40,919
how life is supposed to be.

148
00:11:40,919 --> 00:11:42,919
But we grow out of being teenagers.

149
00:11:42,919 --> 00:11:48,879
And then those truly wonderful years come normally where we find that one that God has

150
00:11:48,879 --> 00:11:52,479
made for us and we're going to share a life with them.

151
00:11:52,479 --> 00:11:57,359
And then we grow out of that season of newlyweds to become young parents.

152
00:11:57,359 --> 00:12:03,079
And it's a challenging season, but it's also one of the greatest seasons of life as we

153
00:12:03,079 --> 00:12:05,879
see those children born into our homes.

154
00:12:05,879 --> 00:12:11,519
And then that season comes of being an empty nester and we don't know what we're going

155
00:12:11,519 --> 00:12:13,299
to do, how we're going to survive.

156
00:12:13,299 --> 00:12:17,319
And then we find out it's a pretty good deal.

157
00:12:17,319 --> 00:12:26,239
And then after being empty nesters, we become seniors and we're almost back to infancy.

158
00:12:26,239 --> 00:12:27,239
Think about it.

159
00:12:27,239 --> 00:12:29,279
You have a point preacher?

160
00:12:29,279 --> 00:12:30,279
Yeah.

161
00:12:30,279 --> 00:12:31,279
Yeah.

162
00:12:31,279 --> 00:12:34,839
We live our lives in seasons.

163
00:12:34,839 --> 00:12:37,139
And they come and they go.

164
00:12:37,139 --> 00:12:41,279
They stay for a while and then we move on to something else.

165
00:12:42,039 --> 00:12:49,159
And some of them are incredibly precious and some of them are incredibly difficult.

166
00:12:49,159 --> 00:12:56,239
David one day was sitting on a hillside tending sheep, creating wonderful psalms and hymns

167
00:12:56,239 --> 00:12:58,999
about the Lord and creation.

168
00:12:58,999 --> 00:13:02,719
But the next moment in life, he's called down to the house.

169
00:13:02,719 --> 00:13:09,319
He stands before Samuel, the judge, the prophet, and he's anointed king.

170
00:13:09,319 --> 00:13:16,599
One moment he's a hero with his foot on Goliath's chest, but the next he's dodging a spear from

171
00:13:16,599 --> 00:13:18,759
King Saul.

172
00:13:18,759 --> 00:13:24,559
The next moment he's a king in Hebron and then Jerusalem and living in a palace.

173
00:13:24,559 --> 00:13:30,439
But the next he's an outcast being chased by his own son.

174
00:13:30,439 --> 00:13:35,839
I'm simply saying that we don't know what tomorrow holds and we're not guaranteed that

175
00:13:35,839 --> 00:13:38,199
tomorrow is a sweet season.

176
00:13:38,199 --> 00:13:43,319
Here's the truth, we're going to pass through some wonderful times, but we're also going

177
00:13:43,319 --> 00:13:48,319
to face some truly difficult times in our lives.

178
00:13:48,319 --> 00:13:56,719
One of my favorite things as a pastor, preacher, was when a young couple would have a child.

179
00:13:56,719 --> 00:14:03,399
And we had a very young congregation and I was often, I did way more weddings than funerals.

180
00:14:03,399 --> 00:14:08,079
And I remember going to the hospital one time and this young couple, he was a Marine and

181
00:14:08,159 --> 00:14:11,799
his wife, they had just had their first child.

182
00:14:11,799 --> 00:14:16,559
And he and I were standing off to the side and she was over in a rocking chair in a little

183
00:14:16,559 --> 00:14:22,079
blue blanket and a little blue beanie, you know, and she was rocking her new little boy.

184
00:14:22,079 --> 00:14:29,079
And the husband and I, we were talking about, I'm quite sure, serious things, maybe football.

185
00:14:29,079 --> 00:14:34,159
And I overheard the wife and she was so softly, she could have cared less about us.

186
00:14:34,159 --> 00:14:37,199
Her attention was that little baby.

187
00:14:37,199 --> 00:14:44,439
And I heard her say something like this, I don't ever want this moment to pass.

188
00:14:44,439 --> 00:14:50,799
I just always want you to be in my arms and my little baby and my little boy.

189
00:14:50,799 --> 00:14:56,759
And I overheard her say that and down inside me as a fundamental Baptist preacher, I wanted

190
00:14:56,759 --> 00:15:03,359
to turn to her and say, well sister, that baby's going to grow up.

191
00:15:03,359 --> 00:15:05,599
It's not always going to be like this.

192
00:15:05,599 --> 00:15:09,519
They're going to grow up and they're going to love somebody else more than you and leave

193
00:15:09,519 --> 00:15:10,519
you.

194
00:15:10,519 --> 00:15:15,879
Aren't you glad I fought the urge to say that?

195
00:15:15,879 --> 00:15:18,519
But that was the truth.

196
00:15:18,519 --> 00:15:20,919
Because life's always moving.

197
00:15:20,919 --> 00:15:22,719
It's always moving.

198
00:15:22,719 --> 00:15:24,679
It never stays the same.

199
00:15:24,679 --> 00:15:29,519
And sometimes we just want to reach out to the Lord and say, leave it here.

200
00:15:29,519 --> 00:15:30,919
Stop moving it.

201
00:15:30,919 --> 00:15:32,599
Stop letting the world turn.

202
00:15:32,599 --> 00:15:36,359
I remember my grandma used to watch her show.

203
00:15:36,359 --> 00:15:41,479
It was a soap opera called As the World Turns and it followed the lives of these people

204
00:15:41,479 --> 00:15:47,079
and they got old and they had problems and they had good days and bad days.

205
00:15:47,079 --> 00:15:51,279
And I began to recognize it was not something you might want to watch, but it was mighty

206
00:15:51,279 --> 00:15:52,919
true in what it said.

207
00:15:52,919 --> 00:15:59,519
The world keeps turning and we never know what tomorrow brings.

208
00:16:00,519 --> 00:16:08,879
But sometimes what tomorrow brings is not easy and not pleasant, but it's part of what

209
00:16:08,879 --> 00:16:13,639
God is allowing and doing in our lives.

210
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:22,559
I am so thankful that in those seasons that are moving and ever-changing, mine are lived

211
00:16:22,559 --> 00:16:25,959
in the hands of God and so are yours.

212
00:16:25,959 --> 00:16:28,479
Think about that with me for a moment.

213
00:16:28,479 --> 00:16:31,759
David's times may have been unstable.

214
00:16:31,759 --> 00:16:38,479
David's life may have been ever-changing, but David's God was stable and unchanging.

215
00:16:38,479 --> 00:16:39,999
Think of words that he used.

216
00:16:39,999 --> 00:16:46,479
He described God as a rock, as a fortress, as a house of defense.

217
00:16:46,479 --> 00:16:52,759
In other words, man, everything is swirling about me, but God never moves.

218
00:16:52,759 --> 00:16:55,239
God never changes.

219
00:16:55,239 --> 00:17:03,199
One of the attributes of God that is so precious to me is that God is immutable.

220
00:17:03,199 --> 00:17:09,999
We often talk about God being omniscient and it's a wonderful truth that God knows everything.

221
00:17:09,999 --> 00:17:15,559
God knows everything about me and God knows everything I need.

222
00:17:15,559 --> 00:17:17,439
God is omnipresent.

223
00:17:17,439 --> 00:17:20,799
I am so thankful God is present with us this morning.

224
00:17:20,799 --> 00:17:26,719
My wife in Charlotte, I'm glad God is present with my wife and with my son as he stands

225
00:17:26,719 --> 00:17:28,159
to preach this morning.

226
00:17:28,159 --> 00:17:31,159
I'm glad that God is present with every missionary.

227
00:17:31,159 --> 00:17:37,439
I'm glad God is present with my kids and grandkids scattered across the country.

228
00:17:37,439 --> 00:17:39,319
God is ever-present.

229
00:17:39,319 --> 00:17:40,719
God is omnipotent.

230
00:17:40,719 --> 00:17:46,239
There's never anything that we face that God cannot care for, God cannot take control of.

231
00:17:46,239 --> 00:17:48,039
God is omnipotent.

232
00:17:48,039 --> 00:17:50,839
All things are possible for God.

233
00:17:50,839 --> 00:17:59,399
And we know those omnis, but sometimes we're not as careful to appreciate that God is immutable.

234
00:17:59,399 --> 00:18:06,399
And as everything swirls around us, God is the same that he's always been.

235
00:18:06,399 --> 00:18:09,759
And God's truth is the same as it's always been.

236
00:18:09,759 --> 00:18:12,639
His mercy endures forever.

237
00:18:12,639 --> 00:18:19,399
He is exactly today what he was yesterday and tomorrow when my life changes, he will

238
00:18:19,399 --> 00:18:22,519
exactly be what he was today.

239
00:18:22,519 --> 00:18:24,439
He never changes.

240
00:18:24,439 --> 00:18:28,399
Now let me mention two aspects of that that's important for us.

241
00:18:28,399 --> 00:18:34,440
God is not only immutable, God is sovereign.

242
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:37,079
Sometimes we're a little bit afraid of that word sovereign.

243
00:18:37,079 --> 00:18:41,279
It's a wonderful word and a wonderful truth.

244
00:18:41,279 --> 00:18:47,639
The word David uses for times is the same word that Daniel uses, and I won't have you

245
00:18:47,639 --> 00:18:49,440
turn there for the sake of time.

246
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:56,679
But it's the same word that Daniel uses when he says this, Daniel answered and said, blessed

247
00:18:56,679 --> 00:19:03,559
be the name of God forever and ever, for wisdom and might are his.

248
00:19:03,559 --> 00:19:09,519
And he changeth the times and the seasons.

249
00:19:09,519 --> 00:19:13,519
He removeth kings and setteth up kings.

250
00:19:13,519 --> 00:19:21,959
He giveth wisdom unto the wise and knowledge to them that know understanding.

251
00:19:21,959 --> 00:19:25,440
Our world seems to be utterly chaotic.

252
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:34,079
But I want you to understand that in the midst of our chaos as we see our world, God is absolutely

253
00:19:34,079 --> 00:19:36,359
in control.

254
00:19:36,359 --> 00:19:40,099
Nothing takes God by surprise.

255
00:19:40,099 --> 00:19:46,759
God is not sitting on the edge of heaven hoping it works out.

256
00:19:46,759 --> 00:19:51,679
God knows exactly where he is taking planet earth.

257
00:19:51,679 --> 00:19:58,279
And by the way, God knows exactly where he is taking you and I.

258
00:19:58,279 --> 00:20:00,039
God is God in the future.

259
00:20:00,039 --> 00:20:01,919
God is God in the past.

260
00:20:01,919 --> 00:20:04,239
God is God in the present.

261
00:20:04,239 --> 00:20:07,519
And God is sovereign over all men.

262
00:20:07,519 --> 00:20:12,059
God knows who he is going to raise up and allow to rule.

263
00:20:12,059 --> 00:20:15,359
But God knows when he's going to take them down

264
00:20:15,359 --> 00:20:17,279
and let someone else rule.

265
00:20:17,279 --> 00:20:22,159
This world is not moving by the manipulative hand of man.

266
00:20:22,159 --> 00:20:26,039
It is moving by the settled story of God.

267
00:20:27,039 --> 00:20:31,079
And it is coming to the place where God is bringing it.

268
00:20:31,079 --> 00:20:35,719
Hey, good news, Jesus is coming again.

269
00:20:38,039 --> 00:20:42,239
We may not like every aspect of how it is coming there,

270
00:20:42,239 --> 00:20:46,519
but it is coming there under God's control.

271
00:20:46,519 --> 00:20:50,479
And sometimes we get so frustrated

272
00:20:50,479 --> 00:20:55,159
and we get maybe so frightened because of the moment,

273
00:20:55,159 --> 00:20:56,839
but you and I must understand

274
00:20:56,839 --> 00:21:00,599
that our times are in God's hands.

275
00:21:00,599 --> 00:21:05,599
And he is a sovereign God moving history his direction.

276
00:21:07,579 --> 00:21:12,519
But let me also say this, God is also a personal God.

277
00:21:13,799 --> 00:21:15,519
Aren't you glad of that?

278
00:21:15,519 --> 00:21:19,839
God is not just some foreboding force.

279
00:21:20,839 --> 00:21:25,519
God is not just some unknowable power.

280
00:21:26,359 --> 00:21:29,319
God is personal.

281
00:21:29,319 --> 00:21:32,679
I love what David says in verse 14.

282
00:21:32,679 --> 00:21:36,879
Thou art my God.

283
00:21:38,119 --> 00:21:40,659
I am so thankful this morning

284
00:21:40,659 --> 00:21:44,959
that I can say God is my God.

285
00:21:46,139 --> 00:21:48,759
I am his son.

286
00:21:50,519 --> 00:21:52,199
I did not get saved as a child.

287
00:21:52,199 --> 00:21:54,159
I wasn't raised in a Christian home.

288
00:21:54,159 --> 00:21:55,279
I have wonderful parents.

289
00:21:55,279 --> 00:21:58,119
Please don't hear me saying that they were not good people.

290
00:21:58,119 --> 00:21:59,319
They were wonderful people.

291
00:21:59,319 --> 00:22:03,159
And dad got saved at 63 years old.

292
00:22:03,159 --> 00:22:04,659
Mom got saved.

293
00:22:04,659 --> 00:22:07,359
My brother got saved and through a series of events,

294
00:22:07,359 --> 00:22:10,979
I got saved, my wife got saved, praise God for it.

295
00:22:10,979 --> 00:22:14,879
We were 23 years old, young parents when we got saved.

296
00:22:14,879 --> 00:22:17,399
And I regret, as long as I live,

297
00:22:17,399 --> 00:22:20,599
I regret that the first 23 years of my life

298
00:22:20,599 --> 00:22:23,279
were not lived under the purposes

299
00:22:23,279 --> 00:22:25,679
and the understanding of who God was.

300
00:22:25,679 --> 00:22:29,839
But I am grateful for this, that I know the dividing line.

301
00:22:29,839 --> 00:22:33,599
I am grateful that I know what it was to live without him

302
00:22:33,599 --> 00:22:37,479
and then to understand my need of him and to be saved

303
00:22:37,479 --> 00:22:40,959
and now to have lived knowing him and him knowing me

304
00:22:40,959 --> 00:22:44,199
and to have the consciousness that I know where I was.

305
00:22:44,199 --> 00:22:46,279
I know how God spoke to me.

306
00:22:46,279 --> 00:22:49,919
I know what my need was and I called out to him to save me

307
00:22:49,919 --> 00:22:54,919
and it's all been different because thou art my God.

308
00:22:57,519 --> 00:22:58,799
What a joy.

309
00:23:01,879 --> 00:23:04,239
He is a personal God.

310
00:23:04,239 --> 00:23:08,359
You see, God is both transcendent and imminent.

311
00:23:08,359 --> 00:23:09,839
What do you mean by that, preacher?

312
00:23:09,839 --> 00:23:12,839
I mean that God is big enough, so big,

313
00:23:12,839 --> 00:23:15,279
that he rules the universe.

314
00:23:16,759 --> 00:23:21,079
But he is so personal that he met with me

315
00:23:21,079 --> 00:23:25,519
in that wonderful apartment I have that you have provided.

316
00:23:26,359 --> 00:23:27,919
He met with me this morning.

317
00:23:29,199 --> 00:23:32,039
50 years in to knowing him, he met with me

318
00:23:32,039 --> 00:23:34,719
and showed me truth from the word of God,

319
00:23:34,719 --> 00:23:37,039
spoke to me about my life.

320
00:23:37,039 --> 00:23:38,719
That's who my God is.

321
00:23:38,719 --> 00:23:41,479
He's big enough to run the universe.

322
00:23:41,479 --> 00:23:45,119
He's big enough to choose kings and put kings down.

323
00:23:45,119 --> 00:23:48,439
He's big enough to control the chaos of this world,

324
00:23:48,439 --> 00:23:51,159
but he's personal enough to meet with me,

325
00:23:52,599 --> 00:23:54,879
to care about my knee hurts.

326
00:23:54,879 --> 00:23:57,239
Would you please feel sorry for me this week?

327
00:23:59,239 --> 00:24:04,239
He's personal enough to know my needs, my heart.

328
00:24:05,599 --> 00:24:07,319
What a God we serve.

329
00:24:08,319 --> 00:24:12,039
You say, well, preacher, if he's so big

330
00:24:12,039 --> 00:24:15,799
that he can run the universe and so sovereign

331
00:24:15,799 --> 00:24:20,239
that everything is planned out and so personal

332
00:24:20,239 --> 00:24:22,839
that he knows where I am, knows what I need,

333
00:24:22,839 --> 00:24:25,919
knows where he's taking me, then I have no part?

334
00:24:26,799 --> 00:24:27,639
Oh, no.

335
00:24:28,599 --> 00:24:32,639
That's where David put this, verse 14.

336
00:24:32,639 --> 00:24:37,559
But I trusted in thee.

337
00:24:37,559 --> 00:24:40,199
It's God's job to run the universe.

338
00:24:40,199 --> 00:24:43,999
It's God's job to be personal and direct me,

339
00:24:43,999 --> 00:24:47,799
but it is my job to trust him.

340
00:24:48,799 --> 00:24:52,559
You see, personal trust in a personal God

341
00:24:52,559 --> 00:24:56,839
and a sovereign God gives us the inner stability

342
00:24:56,839 --> 00:25:00,999
when everything else around us is in upheaval.

343
00:25:02,079 --> 00:25:04,799
In the middle of this chaotic world

344
00:25:04,799 --> 00:25:07,879
where God knows what he's doing, but I don't,

345
00:25:08,839 --> 00:25:12,199
my job is to trust him.

346
00:25:13,879 --> 00:25:14,719
Trust him.

347
00:25:16,319 --> 00:25:18,839
Now, there are times when we trust the Lord

348
00:25:18,839 --> 00:25:21,479
in the middle of the storms and the bad seasons,

349
00:25:21,479 --> 00:25:23,279
the difficult seasons of life,

350
00:25:23,279 --> 00:25:25,279
where we wonder, is God doing anything?

351
00:25:25,279 --> 00:25:26,319
Is God there?

352
00:25:26,319 --> 00:25:28,759
God always is there.

353
00:25:28,759 --> 00:25:31,879
And sometimes when we're in the ship with God

354
00:25:31,879 --> 00:25:35,159
and we cry out, master, carest thou not that we perish,

355
00:25:35,159 --> 00:25:37,799
he rises from the hinder part of the ship

356
00:25:38,679 --> 00:25:41,639
and he walks up and speaks and the waves cease

357
00:25:41,639 --> 00:25:45,719
and the storm stops and we say, oh God, you love me.

358
00:25:45,719 --> 00:25:47,519
It's so wonderful.

359
00:25:48,879 --> 00:25:51,839
But there are other times when we say, Lord,

360
00:25:51,839 --> 00:25:52,799
there's a storm.

361
00:25:54,959 --> 00:25:57,599
And he chooses to let your Clydon blow.

362
00:25:59,079 --> 00:26:03,359
And the storm blows so hard that the ship breaks up.

363
00:26:04,319 --> 00:26:07,799
But in the midst of that storm, God speaks to us

364
00:26:07,799 --> 00:26:10,799
and says, hey, you're going to make it through here

365
00:26:10,799 --> 00:26:13,639
and you're gonna lose the ship, but not your life.

366
00:26:13,639 --> 00:26:15,879
And I know where you are and what you need.

367
00:26:15,879 --> 00:26:18,599
And by the way, when you get cast into the water,

368
00:26:18,599 --> 00:26:20,999
I'm gonna bring a board by.

369
00:26:20,999 --> 00:26:24,799
And you can snatch the board and make it to land, Paul,

370
00:26:24,799 --> 00:26:26,839
but I'm not gonna stop the storm.

371
00:26:26,839 --> 00:26:30,719
And by the way, Paul, got another tough event on the land

372
00:26:30,719 --> 00:26:31,959
because you're gonna make a fire

373
00:26:32,279 --> 00:26:35,039
because you're cold and I'm gonna let a snake bite you.

374
00:26:36,239 --> 00:26:38,879
But Paul, I'm sovereign.

375
00:26:38,879 --> 00:26:42,319
I'm gonna take the venom out and you're not gonna die.

376
00:26:42,319 --> 00:26:44,599
Now, if I were Paul, I'd have said,

377
00:26:46,439 --> 00:26:49,079
let's stop short of the ship breaking up.

378
00:26:50,679 --> 00:26:53,519
Let's stop short of the snake.

379
00:26:53,519 --> 00:26:57,079
And that's when God says, no, no, no, no, understand this.

380
00:26:57,079 --> 00:27:00,159
Paul, your times, they're in my hands.

381
00:27:00,199 --> 00:27:03,279
And I'm doing something that you can't see.

382
00:27:03,279 --> 00:27:06,479
I'm doing something bigger than you can imagine,

383
00:27:06,479 --> 00:27:07,999
but I've got you.

384
00:27:07,999 --> 00:27:12,999
And your job is to trust me in the middle of that storm.

385
00:27:16,799 --> 00:27:19,959
Let me make two observations and I'll be done.

386
00:27:19,959 --> 00:27:23,479
Number one, the time to prepare for trouble

387
00:27:23,479 --> 00:27:24,679
is before you're in it,

388
00:27:27,799 --> 00:27:29,799
especially in the matter of salvation.

389
00:27:31,119 --> 00:27:32,399
If you're here this morning

390
00:27:32,399 --> 00:27:35,879
and you can't point to that time in your life.

391
00:27:36,919 --> 00:27:40,079
Now, not everybody has to know a date.

392
00:27:40,079 --> 00:27:42,119
Not everybody has to know the exact moment

393
00:27:42,119 --> 00:27:45,279
the clock struck when you got saved.

394
00:27:45,279 --> 00:27:50,279
But being born again is an important moment.

395
00:27:52,519 --> 00:27:56,279
We may not know what time it was or what day it was,

396
00:27:56,279 --> 00:27:59,879
but when we get saved, we're acknowledging to the Lord

397
00:28:00,119 --> 00:28:01,199
that I'm a sinner.

398
00:28:02,359 --> 00:28:06,559
And my sin has broken any relationship with you.

399
00:28:06,559 --> 00:28:11,559
And if I bear my sin, you can't be in the presence of sin.

400
00:28:11,559 --> 00:28:13,639
And if I bear my own sin,

401
00:28:13,639 --> 00:28:15,839
I can never come into your presence.

402
00:28:17,399 --> 00:28:20,999
And God answers back, but I've remedied that

403
00:28:22,039 --> 00:28:25,239
because I sent my son to earth

404
00:28:25,239 --> 00:28:28,759
and my son loving you so much

405
00:28:28,799 --> 00:28:31,119
went to a cross at Calvary

406
00:28:31,119 --> 00:28:34,359
where all sin was poured out on him.

407
00:28:34,359 --> 00:28:37,119
And instead of me forsaking you,

408
00:28:37,119 --> 00:28:40,359
instead of you not being able to be in my presence,

409
00:28:40,359 --> 00:28:42,799
I forsook my own son.

410
00:28:42,799 --> 00:28:46,000
My God, my God, why has thou forsaken me?

411
00:28:46,919 --> 00:28:51,919
And in that moment, sin was judged and sin was paid for

412
00:28:52,239 --> 00:28:55,799
and the price of sin, the penalty of sin was paid.

413
00:28:55,799 --> 00:28:57,399
My son died.

414
00:28:59,479 --> 00:29:01,079
And if you'll look to my son,

415
00:29:02,039 --> 00:29:04,759
and see, that's a conscious act, isn't it?

416
00:29:04,759 --> 00:29:07,440
That's not something we're given from our parents.

417
00:29:07,440 --> 00:29:10,079
That's not something that we just grow into.

418
00:29:10,079 --> 00:29:12,279
It's a conscious act.

419
00:29:12,279 --> 00:29:15,839
I don't know what day, I'm not sure what time it was,

420
00:29:15,839 --> 00:29:19,479
but I remember hearing the gospel somehow

421
00:29:19,479 --> 00:29:21,559
and I remember that moment in my life,

422
00:29:21,559 --> 00:29:23,839
maybe alone after the service,

423
00:29:23,839 --> 00:29:25,919
maybe alone after someone had talked to me,

424
00:29:25,919 --> 00:29:27,759
maybe alone after I had read something.

425
00:29:27,839 --> 00:29:30,119
I remember that moment in my life

426
00:29:30,119 --> 00:29:33,119
that I acknowledged what God said was true.

427
00:29:34,320 --> 00:29:37,559
My sin separates me from you.

428
00:29:39,440 --> 00:29:40,880
And I can't change that.

429
00:29:42,199 --> 00:29:45,759
And I acknowledge that you sent your son, Jesus,

430
00:29:45,759 --> 00:29:48,279
who died in my place.

431
00:29:48,279 --> 00:29:53,119
And if I will simply look to what you did for me

432
00:29:53,119 --> 00:29:55,000
and receive that gift,

433
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:57,759
acknowledge my need as a sinner

434
00:29:57,759 --> 00:30:00,000
and acknowledge the work of your son.

435
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:02,900
on the cross at Calvary in a transaction

436
00:30:02,900 --> 00:30:06,579
I'll never understand fully until I get to heaven.

437
00:30:06,579 --> 00:30:11,420
My sin is paid for in what Jesus did

438
00:30:11,420 --> 00:30:15,060
and Jesus' righteousness, the Bible word,

439
00:30:15,060 --> 00:30:20,059
is imputed to me and I now bear the righteousness of Jesus

440
00:30:20,659 --> 00:30:24,219
as he bears my son and when God looks at me,

441
00:30:24,219 --> 00:30:27,420
he no longer sees sinful Mike Edwards,

442
00:30:27,420 --> 00:30:30,180
he sees the righteousness of Jesus

443
00:30:31,620 --> 00:30:34,020
and on the basis of that transaction,

444
00:30:35,060 --> 00:30:39,500
I can get in heaven, I can be present with the Lord forever.

445
00:30:39,500 --> 00:30:44,340
Hey, that's a conscious moment of decision in our lives

446
00:30:45,599 --> 00:30:47,959
and if you're here this morning

447
00:30:47,959 --> 00:30:50,580
and you've never had that moment in your life,

448
00:30:51,459 --> 00:30:53,860
I'm telling you it's available to you today.

449
00:30:54,860 --> 00:30:57,459
God didn't stop doing that in 1950.

450
00:30:58,500 --> 00:31:01,860
God didn't stop saving people that way in 2000.

451
00:31:01,860 --> 00:31:05,500
God is saving people like that in 2025

452
00:31:05,500 --> 00:31:09,220
and he is here and it's a decision that you've gotta make,

453
00:31:09,220 --> 00:31:11,019
oh, not to save yourself

454
00:31:11,019 --> 00:31:14,360
but to receive what God has already done.

455
00:31:15,540 --> 00:31:16,779
Let me move on quickly.

456
00:31:17,720 --> 00:31:20,699
I'm also saying that the time to prepare for trouble

457
00:31:21,699 --> 00:31:23,860
is before it happens for believers.

458
00:31:26,099 --> 00:31:29,819
Sometimes in the good seasons of life, I'll speak for me,

459
00:31:29,819 --> 00:31:32,459
sometimes in the good seasons of life,

460
00:31:32,459 --> 00:31:35,379
I forget that there may be a difficult season coming.

461
00:31:36,739 --> 00:31:39,220
I just think life will always be like this.

462
00:31:39,220 --> 00:31:41,940
It'll always be okay but it won't always be okay.

463
00:31:44,739 --> 00:31:48,559
This body will wear out, fortunes change,

464
00:31:49,400 --> 00:31:52,120
things move in and out of our lives

465
00:31:52,120 --> 00:31:55,839
and sometimes in the good, easier seasons,

466
00:31:55,839 --> 00:31:57,120
you know what I do?

467
00:31:57,120 --> 00:32:00,199
I forget how desperately I need the Lord

468
00:32:01,879 --> 00:32:04,760
and I become a little too confident in myself

469
00:32:06,519 --> 00:32:07,940
and then the crisis hits.

470
00:32:09,479 --> 00:32:12,039
And I'm saying to you, there's never a day that we live

471
00:32:12,039 --> 00:32:14,100
that we don't desperately need the Lord.

472
00:32:14,100 --> 00:32:17,320
There's never a day that we walk and work

473
00:32:17,320 --> 00:32:20,320
and go through life where we don't need to call out

474
00:32:20,320 --> 00:32:24,240
to the Lord and be absolutely dependent on him

475
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:26,399
and may you and I be very careful

476
00:32:26,399 --> 00:32:30,800
that we do not live our lives thinking we can handle it

477
00:32:32,160 --> 00:32:34,039
and then that season comes.

478
00:32:35,399 --> 00:32:36,880
I'd say secondly this,

479
00:32:37,919 --> 00:32:41,240
though we may at times be overwhelmed, God never is.

480
00:32:42,960 --> 00:32:46,820
And you and I must practice trusting the Lord.

481
00:32:47,759 --> 00:32:52,360
In the good seasons but also in the difficult seasons.

482
00:32:53,559 --> 00:32:55,679
David was writing psalms when it was just

483
00:32:55,679 --> 00:32:57,919
a beautiful hillside with him and his sheep.

484
00:32:59,520 --> 00:33:01,559
David was singing and praying those psalms

485
